%%Page: 5 6
5 5 bop 442 2630 a @beginspecial 20 @llx 170 @lly 592
@urx 622 @ury 3528 @rwi @setspecial
%%BeginDocument: figiowa1.ps
150 dict begin gsave
/bd{bind def}def
/PVer 3200 def
% drawing commands
/I{Coord SetPage 1 setlinecap 1 setlinejoin
X    LineTypes{RastersPerPoint ScaleArray}forall
X    /Helvetica findfont
X    PointSize RastersPerPoint mul Cex mul scalefont setfont
X    /Colors GColors def
}bd
/BWOp{
X    bw{currentrgbcolor add add 2.9 gt{1}{0}ifelse setgray}if
X    exec
X    bw{CurSc Sc}if
}bd
/IBu{}def
/B{newpath}bd
/E{{stroke}BWOp}bd
/C{currentpoint Penup{newpath}{E}ifelse moveto}bd
/F{closepath eofill}bd
/M{moveto}bd
/L{lineto}bd
/Pu{load /XEQ exch def /Penup true def}bd
/Pd{/XEQ{}def /Penup false def}bd
/Px{currentdict /XEQ known{XEQ}if}bd
/h{Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/j{neg Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/k{exch neg exch Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/l{neg exch neg exch Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/m{moveto Penup{Px}if}bd
/x{0 Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/y{0 exch Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/w{neg x}bd
/z{neg y}bd
/a{B M dup y exch x neg y closepath}bd
/b{a eofill}bd
/c{a E}bd
/A{PageBegin BackCol 0 ge
X    {CurSc gsave 0 SC Page aload pop
X    exch 4 -1 roll dup 5 1 roll sub 3 1 roll exch dup 4 1 roll sub 4 2 roll b
X    grestore SC}if
}bd
/Ph{gsave Pch-x Pch-y rmoveto Show grestore}bd
/Pc{Pch Ph}bd
/T{/Adjust exch def gsave translate StringRot rotate 0 0 moveto
X    dup stringwidth pop neg Adjust mul 0 rmoveto
X    currentpoint translate TextShow grestore}bd
/X{erasepage InPage{PageEnd}if}bd
/Z{gsave showpage grestore PageEnd}bd
/W{grestore end}bd
% parameter setting commands
/saveAt{Attr begin
X    /Atlinewidth currentlinewidth def
X    /Atfont currentfont def
X    /Atdash currentdash 2 array astore def
X    /AtSc CurSc def
end}bd
/restAt{Attr begin
X    Atlinewidth Atfont Atdash AtSc
X    end
X    SC aload pop setdash setfont setlinewidth
}bd
/SC{dup dup 0 eq
X    {pop BackIdx
X        {BackCol dup 0 lt {pop 1 setgray} {Sc}ifelse}
X        {/Colors BColor def 1 Sc}ifelse}
X    {/Colors GColors def Sc}ifelse
X    /CurSc exch def
}bd
/St{1 sub LineTypes dup 3 1 roll length Rem floor get 0 setdash}bd
/Sw{abs 2 div RastersPerPoint mul setlinewidth SetClip}bd
/Sp{dup 42 eq{pop IBu}{Pch exch 0 exch put SetPchSize}ifelse}bd
/Sx{dup Cex div /Ratio exch def
X     /Cex exch def
X     currentfont Ratio scalefont setfont
X     /Pch-x Pch-x Ratio mul def
X     /Pch-y Pch-y Ratio mul def
X     /Text-y Text-y Ratio mul def}bd
/So{4 1 roll exch 4 -1 roll Plot astore pop SetClip}bd
/Sg{4 1 roll exch 4 -1 roll Figure astore pop SetClip}bd
/Sr{/StringRot exch def}bd
/Sh{/CharRot exch def}bd
/Sd{0 eq /ClipToPlot exch def SetClip}bd
/Iv{/InPage false def/Clip 4 array def/Page 4 array def
X    /Figure [0 0 1 1] def/Plot [0 0 1 1] def/ClipToPlot true def
X    /Cex 1 def/Outline false def
X    /Pch 1 string def/Pch-x 0 def/Pch-y 0 def/Text-y 0 def
X    /LineTypes [ % in default units
X        [] [1 2] [4 4] [8 4] [13 3] [16 2 2 2] [8 2 2 2] [1 13] [6 5] [12 4]
X    ] def
X    /Attr 5 dict def/CurSc 1 def/Penup false def/XEQ{}def
}bd
/Rem{2 copy div floor mul sub floor cvi}bd
/RastersPerPoint{RastersPerInch 72 div}bd
/ScaleArray{/Factor exch def /Array exch def
X    0 1 Array length 1 sub
X    {dup Array exch get Factor mul Array 3 1 roll put}for}bd
/Coord{Region aload pop /uy exch def /ux exch def /ly exch def /lx exch def
X    uy ly sub ux lx sub Landscape{exch}if /Width exch def /Height exch def
X    lx ly translate Landscape{90 rotate 0 Height neg translate}if
X    1 RastersPerPoint div dup scale}bd
/SetPchSize{gsave
X    newpath 0 0 moveto Pch false charpath flattenpath pathbbox
X    exch 3 1 roll
X    add 2 div neg /Pch-y exch def
X    add 2 div neg /Pch-x exch def
X    grestore}bd
/Show{Outline{false charpath E}{{show}BWOp}ifelse}bd
/SimpleShow{0 Text-y 2 div neg rmoveto Show}bd
/FancyShow{
X    /RotDiff exch def
X    /Cos RotDiff cos abs def
X    /Sin RotDiff sin abs def
X    {
X        ( ) dup 0 4 -1 roll put
X        dup stringwidth pop /CharWidth exch def
X        Cos 0 eq{
X            Text-y Sin div
X        }{
X            Sin 0 eq{
X                CharWidth Cos div
X            }{
X                Text-y Sin div dup
X                CharWidth Cos div dup
X                4 1 roll lt{exch pop}{pop}ifelse
X            }ifelse
X        }ifelse 2 div /CharDist exch def
X        CharDist 0 translate 0 0 moveto
X        gsave
X            RotDiff rotate
X            CharWidth 2 div neg Text-y 2 div neg rmoveto
X            Show
X        grestore
X        CharDist 0 translate 0 0 moveto
X    }forall
}bd
/TextShow{
X    CharRot StringRot sub dup 0 eq{pop SimpleShow}{FancyShow}ifelse
}bd
/BoxClip{/CLW currentlinewidth def
X    2{CLW add 4 1 roll}repeat
X    2{CLW sub 4 1 roll}repeat
X    % initclip
X    saveAt grestore gsave restAt
X    newpath 2 index exch 2 index exch dup 6 index exch
X    moveto 3{lineto}repeat closepath clip newpath}bd
/Subregion{
X    7 dict begin/A exch def/Uy exch def/Ux exch def/Ly exch def/Lx exch def
X    Ux Lx sub A 0 get mul Lx add
X    Uy Ly sub A 1 get mul Ly add
X    Ux Lx sub A 2 get mul Lx add
X    Uy Ly sub A 3 get mul Ly add end}bd
/SetFigure{Page aload pop Figure Subregion}bd
/SetPlot{SetFigure Plot Subregion}bd
/SetClip{ClipToPlot{SetPlot}{SetFigure}ifelse BoxClip}bd
/SetPage{0 0 Width Height Page astore RastersPerPoint ScaleArray}bd
/PageBegin{save /PageContext exch def /InPage true def gsave}bd
/PageEnd{grestore PageContext restore /InPage false def}bd
/SImage{
X    dup /Bits exch def 8 exch idiv /PerByte exch def
X    /Ht exch def /Wid exch def
X    1 Wid div 1 Ht div scale
X    /saveSc CurSc def /Colors IColors def
X    /curstr Wid PerByte add 1 sub PerByte idiv string def
X    /MaskByte 16#ff Bits 8 sub bitshift def
X    1 1 Ht{
X        currentfile curstr readhexstring pop pop
X        /CurPos 0 def
X        /Left PerByte def
X        1 1 Wid{
X            Left PerByte eq{
X                /CurByte curstr CurPos get def
X                /MaskMove -8 Bits add def
X                /CurPos CurPos 1 add def
X            }if
X            CurByte MaskMove bitshift MaskByte and
X            dup 0 gt{
X                Sc
X                exch dup 3 1 roll B M 1 z 1 w 1 y F
X            }{pop pop}ifelse
X            Left 1 sub dup /Left exch def 0 le
X            {/Left PerByte def}
X            {/MaskMove MaskMove Bits add def}ifelse
X        }for
X        pop
X    }for
X    /Colors GColors def saveSc Sc
}bd
/Ic {} bd
/Sc {
X    dup dup 1 lt exch 0 ge and
X    {1 exch sub setgray}  % explicit gray level [0,1)
X    {1 sub Colors dup 3 1 roll length Rem floor get
X     dup type /arraytype eq {aload pop setrgbcolor} {setgray} ifelse
X    } ifelse
} bd
/If {} bd
/Sf {dup 0 lt /Outline exch def abs
X     1 sub Fonts dup 3 1 roll length Rem floor get
X     findfont PointSize Cex mul RastersPerPoint mul scalefont dup setfont
X     dup /FontMatrix get /Matrix exch def /FontBBox get aload pop
X     Matrix transform 4 2 roll Matrix transform
X     exch pop add /Text-y exch def pop SetPchSize} bd
% fixed controlling parameters
/Landscape false def
/Region [20.88 170.755 591.12 621.245] def
/bw statusdict begin /processcolors where
{pop processcolors} {1} ifelse end 1 eq
X def
/RastersPerInch 300 def
/PointSize 14 def
/Fonts [
X	/Helvetica
X	/Courier
X	/Times-Roman
X	/Helvetica-Oblique
X	/Helvetica-Bold
X	/Helvetica-BoldOblique
X	/Courier-Oblique
X	/Courier-Bold
X	/Courier-BoldOblique
X	/Times-Italic
X	/Times-Bold
X	/Times-BoldItalic
X	/Symbol
X	/AvantGarde-Book
X	/AvantGarde-BookOblique
X	/AvantGarde-Demi
X	/AvantGarde-DemiOblique
X	/Bookman-Demi
X	/Bookman-DemiItalic
X	/Bookman-Light
X	/Bookman-LightItalic
X	/Helvetica-Narrow
X	/Helvetica-Narrow-Bold
X	/Helvetica-Narrow-BoldOblique
X	/Helvetica-Narrow-Oblique
X	/NewCenturySchlbk-Roman
X	/NewCenturySchlbk-Bold
X	/NewCenturySchlbk-Italic
X	/NewCenturySchlbk-BoldItalic
X	/Palatino-Roman
X	/Palatino-Bold
X	/Palatino-Italic
X	/Palatino-BoldItalic
X	/ZapfChancery-MediumItalic
X	/ZapfDingbats
] def
/GColors [
X	0
X	0.6
X	0.3
X	0.9
X	0.4
X	0.7
X	0.1
X	0.5
X	0.8
X	0.2
] def
/BackIdx true def
/BackCol -1 def
/IColors [
X	0.933333
X	0.866667
X	0.8
X	0.733333
X	0.666667
X	0.6
X	0.533333
X	0.466667
X	0.4
X	0.333333
X	0.266667
X	0.2
X	0.133333
X	0.0666667
X	0
] def
/Colors GColors def
/IBu {Pch 0 8#267 put SetPchSize} def
/Bu {Pc} def
X
% all initialization action here
Iv I
currentdict /Ic known {Ic} if
currentdict /If known {If} if

%%Page: 6 7
6 6 bop 442 2630 a @beginspecial 20 @llx 170 @lly 592
@urx 622 @ury 3528 @rwi @setspecial
%%BeginDocument: figiowa2.ps
150 dict begin gsave
/bd{bind def}def
/PVer 3200 def
% drawing commands
/I{Coord SetPage 1 setlinecap 1 setlinejoin
X    LineTypes{RastersPerPoint ScaleArray}forall
X    /Helvetica findfont
X    PointSize RastersPerPoint mul Cex mul scalefont setfont
X    /Colors GColors def
}bd
/BWOp{
X    bw{currentrgbcolor add add 2.9 gt{1}{0}ifelse setgray}if
X    exec
X    bw{CurSc Sc}if
}bd
/IBu{}def
/B{newpath}bd
/E{{stroke}BWOp}bd
/C{currentpoint Penup{newpath}{E}ifelse moveto}bd
/F{closepath eofill}bd
/M{moveto}bd
/L{lineto}bd
/Pu{load /XEQ exch def /Penup true def}bd
/Pd{/XEQ{}def /Penup false def}bd
/Px{currentdict /XEQ known{XEQ}if}bd
/h{Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/j{neg Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/k{exch neg exch Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/l{neg exch neg exch Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/m{moveto Penup{Px}if}bd
/x{0 Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/y{0 exch Penup{rmoveto Px}{rlineto}ifelse}bd
/w{neg x}bd
/z{neg y}bd
/a{B M dup y exch x neg y closepath}bd
/b{a eofill}bd
/c{a E}bd
/A{PageBegin BackCol 0 ge
X    {CurSc gsave 0 SC Page aload pop
X    exch 4 -1 roll dup 5 1 roll sub 3 1 roll exch dup 4 1 roll sub 4 2 roll b
X    grestore SC}if
}bd
/Ph{gsave Pch-x Pch-y rmoveto Show grestore}bd
/Pc{Pch Ph}bd
/T{/Adjust exch def gsave translate StringRot rotate 0 0 moveto
X    dup stringwidth pop neg Adjust mul 0 rmoveto
X    currentpoint translate TextShow grestore}bd
/X{erasepage InPage{PageEnd}if}bd
/Z{gsave showpage grestore PageEnd}bd
/W{grestore end}bd
% parameter setting commands
/saveAt{Attr begin
X    /Atlinewidth currentlinewidth def
X    /Atfont currentfont def
X    /Atdash currentdash 2 array astore def
X    /AtSc CurSc def
end}bd
/restAt{Attr begin
X    Atlinewidth Atfont Atdash AtSc
X    end
X    SC aload pop setdash setfont setlinewidth
}bd
/SC{dup dup 0 eq
X    {pop BackIdx
X        {BackCol dup 0 lt {pop 1 setgray} {Sc}ifelse}
X        {/Colors BColor def 1 Sc}ifelse}
X    {/Colors GColors def Sc}ifelse
X    /CurSc exch def
}bd
/St{1 sub LineTypes dup 3 1 roll length Rem floor get 0 setdash}bd
/Sw{abs 2 div RastersPerPoint mul setlinewidth SetClip}bd
/Sp{dup 42 eq{pop IBu}{Pch exch 0 exch put SetPchSize}ifelse}bd
/Sx{dup Cex div /Ratio exch def
X     /Cex exch def
X     currentfont Ratio scalefont setfont
X     /Pch-x Pch-x Ratio mul def
X     /Pch-y Pch-y Ratio mul def
X     /Text-y Text-y Ratio mul def}bd
/So{4 1 roll exch 4 -1 roll Plot astore pop SetClip}bd
/Sg{4 1 roll exch 4 -1 roll Figure astore pop SetClip}bd
/Sr{/StringRot exch def}bd
/Sh{/CharRot exch def}bd
/Sd{0 eq /ClipToPlot exch def SetClip}bd
/Iv{/InPage false def/Clip 4 array def/Page 4 array def
X    /Figure [0 0 1 1] def/Plot [0 0 1 1] def/ClipToPlot true def
X    /Cex 1 def/Outline false def
X    /Pch 1 string def/Pch-x 0 def/Pch-y 0 def/Text-y 0 def
X    /LineTypes [ % in default units
X        [] [1 2] [4 4] [8 4] [13 3] [16 2 2 2] [8 2 2 2] [1 13] [6 5] [12 4]
X    ] def
X    /Attr 5 dict def/CurSc 1 def/Penup false def/XEQ{}def
}bd
/Rem{2 copy div floor mul sub floor cvi}bd
/RastersPerPoint{RastersPerInch 72 div}bd
/ScaleArray{/Factor exch def /Array exch def
X    0 1 Array length 1 sub
X    {dup Array exch get Factor mul Array 3 1 roll put}for}bd
/Coord{Region aload pop /uy exch def /ux exch def /ly exch def /lx exch def
X    uy ly sub ux lx sub Landscape{exch}if /Width exch def /Height exch def
X    lx ly translate Landscape{90 rotate 0 Height neg translate}if
X    1 RastersPerPoint div dup scale}bd
/SetPchSize{gsave
X    newpath 0 0 moveto Pch false charpath flattenpath pathbbox
X    exch 3 1 roll
X    add 2 div neg /Pch-y exch def
X    add 2 div neg /Pch-x exch def
X    grestore}bd
/Show{Outline{false charpath E}{{show}BWOp}ifelse}bd
/SimpleShow{0 Text-y 2 div neg rmoveto Show}bd
/FancyShow{
X    /RotDiff exch def
X    /Cos RotDiff cos abs def
X    /Sin RotDiff sin abs def
X    {
X        ( ) dup 0 4 -1 roll put
X        dup stringwidth pop /CharWidth exch def
X        Cos 0 eq{
X            Text-y Sin div
X        }{
X            Sin 0 eq{
X                CharWidth Cos div
X            }{
X                Text-y Sin div dup
X                CharWidth Cos div dup
X                4 1 roll lt{exch pop}{pop}ifelse
X            }ifelse
X        }ifelse 2 div /CharDist exch def
X        CharDist 0 translate 0 0 moveto
X        gsave
X            RotDiff rotate
X            CharWidth 2 div neg Text-y 2 div neg rmoveto
X            Show
X        grestore
X        CharDist 0 translate 0 0 moveto
X    }forall
}bd
/TextShow{
X    CharRot StringRot sub dup 0 eq{pop SimpleShow}{FancyShow}ifelse
}bd
/BoxClip{/CLW currentlinewidth def
X    2{CLW add 4 1 roll}repeat
X    2{CLW sub 4 1 roll}repeat
X    % initclip
X    saveAt grestore gsave restAt
X    newpath 2 index exch 2 index exch dup 6 index exch
X    moveto 3{lineto}repeat closepath clip newpath}bd
/Subregion{
X    7 dict begin/A exch def/Uy exch def/Ux exch def/Ly exch def/Lx exch def
X    Ux Lx sub A 0 get mul Lx add
X    Uy Ly sub A 1 get mul Ly add
X    Ux Lx sub A 2 get mul Lx add
X    Uy Ly sub A 3 get mul Ly add end}bd
/SetFigure{Page aload pop Figure Subregion}bd
/SetPlot{SetFigure Plot Subregion}bd
/SetClip{ClipToPlot{SetPlot}{SetFigure}ifelse BoxClip}bd
/SetPage{0 0 Width Height Page astore RastersPerPoint ScaleArray}bd
/PageBegin{save /PageContext exch def /InPage true def gsave}bd
/PageEnd{grestore PageContext restore /InPage false def}bd
/SImage{
X    dup /Bits exch def 8 exch idiv /PerByte exch def
X    /Ht exch def /Wid exch def
X    1 Wid div 1 Ht div scale
X    /saveSc CurSc def /Colors IColors def
X    /curstr Wid PerByte add 1 sub PerByte idiv string def
X    /MaskByte 16#ff Bits 8 sub bitshift def
X    1 1 Ht{
X        currentfile curstr readhexstring pop pop
X        /CurPos 0 def
X        /Left PerByte def
X        1 1 Wid{
X            Left PerByte eq{
X                /CurByte curstr CurPos get def
X                /MaskMove -8 Bits add def
X                /CurPos CurPos 1 add def
X            }if
X            CurByte MaskMove bitshift MaskByte and
X            dup 0 gt{
X                Sc
X                exch dup 3 1 roll B M 1 z 1 w 1 y F
X            }{pop pop}ifelse
X            Left 1 sub dup /Left exch def 0 le
X            {/Left PerByte def}
X            {/MaskMove MaskMove Bits add def}ifelse
X        }for
X        pop
X    }for
X    /Colors GColors def saveSc Sc
}bd
/Ic {} bd
/Sc {
X    dup dup 1 lt exch 0 ge and
X    {1 exch sub setgray}  % explicit gray level [0,1)
X    {1 sub Colors dup 3 1 roll length Rem floor get
X     dup type /arraytype eq {aload pop setrgbcolor} {setgray} ifelse
X    } ifelse
} bd
/If {} bd
/Sf {dup 0 lt /Outline exch def abs
X     1 sub Fonts dup 3 1 roll length Rem floor get
X     findfont PointSize Cex mul RastersPerPoint mul scalefont dup setfont
X     dup /FontMatrix get /Matrix exch def /FontBBox get aload pop
X     Matrix transform 4 2 roll Matrix transform
X     exch pop add /Text-y exch def pop SetPchSize} bd
% fixed controlling parameters
/Landscape false def
/Region [20.88 170.755 591.12 621.245] def
/bw statusdict begin /processcolors where
{pop processcolors} {1} ifelse end 1 eq
X def
/RastersPerInch 300 def
/PointSize 14 def
/Fonts [
X	/Helvetica
X	/Courier
X	/Times-Roman
X	/Helvetica-Oblique
X	/Helvetica-Bold
X	/Helvetica-BoldOblique
X	/Courier-Oblique
X	/Courier-Bold
X	/Courier-BoldOblique
X	/Times-Italic
X	/Times-Bold
X	/Times-BoldItalic
X	/Symbol

  chmod 0644 'Lasso2/Doc/Doc/Manual.ps' ||

    echo "Lasso2/Doc/Doc/Manual.ps: original size 415020, current size $shar_count"

#line 185 "qr.nw"
static void qr_incr(void) {
X  qr_max_size += QR_CHUNK;
X  
X  /* reallocate R always */
X  rmat = Realloc(rmat,qr_max_size*(qr_max_size+1)/2,double);
X  if(rmat==NULL)
X    ERRMSG("qr_incr", no_dyn_mem_message);
X    
X  /* reallocate Q only if necessary and only to maximal necessary size */
X  if( qr_max_size >= q_nrow){
X    if( qr_max_size-QR_CHUNK < q_nrow){
X      qmat = Realloc(qmat,q_nrow*q_nrow,double);
X      if(qmat==NULL)
X        ERRMSG("qr_incr", no_dyn_mem_message);
X    }
X  }else{
X    qmat = Realloc(qmat,q_nrow*qr_max_size,double);
X    if(qmat==NULL)
X      ERRMSG("qr_incr", no_dyn_mem_message);
X  }
}

The data gives the pre-season and three growing months' precipitation,
the mean temperatures for the three growing months and harvest month,
the year, and the yield of wheat for the USA state of Iowa, for the
years 1930--1962.
X.SH "DATA DESCRIPTION"

X.AG Year

X.AG Temp2

X.AG Temp3

X.AG Rain3
Rainfall for the third growing month (in.)
X.AG Temp4
Mean temperature for the harvest month (deg. F)
X.AG Yield
Yield of wheat in Iowa for the given year (bush./acre)
X.SH CATEGORY
Multiple regression; diagnostics.
X.SH SOURCE
CAED Report, 1964.  Quoted in Draper and Smith, Applied Regression
Analysis.

X.FN gcv.l1ce
X.TL
Use `gcv()' on a `l1ce' object.
X.CS
gcv(object, type = c("OPT", "Tibshirani"), gen.inverse.diag = 0)
X.RA
X.AG object
a `l1ce' object
X.OA
X.AG type
whether to use the covariance formula of Osborne, Presnell and Turlach
or the formula of Tibshirani
X.AG gen.inverse.diag
if Tibshirani's formula for the covariance matrix is used, this value
is used for the diagonal elements of the generalised inverse that
appears in the formula that corresponds to parameters estimated to be
zero.  The default is 0, i.e. use the Moore-Penrose inverse.
Tibshirani's code uses gen.inverse.diag=1e11.
X.DN
This is a method for the function `gcv()' for objects inheriting
from class `l1ce'.
See `gcv' for the general behavior of this function.
X.SE
None
X.DT
See documentation.
X.WR

# ============= Lasso2/gl1ce.d ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/gl1ce.d' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/gl1ce.d (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/gl1ce.d (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/gl1ce.d' &&
X.BG
X.FN gl1ce
X.TL
Fit a generalized regression problem while imposing an L1 constraint on the 
parameters
X.DN
Returns an object of class `gl1ce' that represents a fit of a generealized
linear model while imposing an L1 constraint on the parameters.
X.CS
gl1ce(formula, data=sys.parent(), weights, subset, na.action, 
family=gaussian, control=glm.control(...), sweep.out= ~ 1, x=F, y=T, 
contrasts=NULL, standardize=T, guess.constrained.coefficients=double(p), 
bound=0.5, ...)
X.RA
X.AG formula
a formula object, with the response on the left hand side of a `~' operator, 
and the terms, separated by a `+' operator, on the right hand side. 
X.OA
X.AG data
a `data.frame' in which to interpret the variables named in the
formula, the `weights', the `subset' and the `sweep.out' argument.
If this is missing, then the variables in the formula should be on the
search list.
X.AG weights
vector of observation weights.
The length of `weights' must be the same as the number of observations.
The weights must be strictly positive, since zero weights are ambiguous, 
compared to use of the `subset' argument.
X.AG subset
expression saying which subset of the rows of the data should be used in the 
fit.  This can be a logical vector (which is replicated to have length equal
to the number of observations), or a numeric vector indicating which 
observation numbers are to be included, or a character vector of the row names
to be included.  All observations are included by default.
X.AG na.action
This is applied to the `model.frame' after any `subset' argument has been used.
The default (with `na.fail') is to create an error if any missing values are 
found.  A possible alternative is `na.omit', which deletes observations
that contain one or more missing values.
X.AG family
a family object - a list of functions and expressions for defining the link and
variance functions, initialization and iterative weights.  Families supported
are gaussian, binomial, poisson, Gamma, inverse.gaussian and quasi.  Functions
like binomial produce a family object, but can be given without the 
parentheses. Family functions can take arguments, as in binomial(link=probit).
X.AG control
a list of iteration and algorithmic  constants.  See glm.control for their 
names and default values.  These can also be set as arguments to gl1ce itself.
X.AG sweep.out
a formula object, variables whose parameters are not put under the
constraint are swept out first.  The variables should appear on the
right of a `~' operator and be separated by `+' operators.  Default is
`~1', i.e. the constant term is not under the constraint.  If this
parameter is `NULL', then all parameters are put under the constraint.
X.AG x
logical flag: if `TRUE', the model matrix is returned in component `x'. 
X.AG y
logical flag: if `TRUE', the response is returned in component `y'.
X.AG contrasts
a list giving contrasts for some or all of the factors appearing in the model 
formula. The elements of the list should have the same name as the variable
and should be either a contrast matrix (specifically, any full-rank
matrix with as many rows as there are levels in the factor),
or else a function to compute such a matrix given the number of levels.
X.AG standardize
logical flag: if `TRUE', then the columns of the model matrix that
correspond to parameters that are constrained are standardized to have
empirical variance one.  The standardization is done after taking
possible weights into account and after sweeping out variables whose
parameters are not constrained.
X.AG guess.constrained.coefficients
initial guess for the parameters that are constrained. 
X.AG bound
numeric, either a single number or a vector: the constraint(s) that
is/are put onto the L1 norm of the parameters. 
X.RT
an object of class `gl1ce' is returned.
See `gl1ce.object' for details.
X.SE
None
X.WR
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/gl1ce.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/gl1ce.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/gl1ce.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/gl1ce.d'`"
  test 3828 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/gl1ce.d: original size 3828, current size $shar_count"
fi
# ============= Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d' &&
X.BG D
X.FN gl1ce.object
X.TL
Generalized L1 Constrained Estimation Model Object
X.DN
These are objects of class `gl1ce'
They represent the fit of a generalized regression model under an L1 constraint
on (some of the parameters).
X.SH GENERATION
This class of objects is returned from the `gl1ce' function
to represent a fitted model.
X.SH METHODS
The `gl1ce' class of objects has methods for the following generic
functions:
X.br
`deviance', `predict', `print', `residuals', `summary'.  Other generic 
functions are inherited from the class `l1ce'.
X.SH STRUCTURE
The following components must be included in a legitimate `gl1ce' object.
X.RC coefficients
the coefficients of the fit of the response to the columns of the model matrix.
The names of the coefficients are the names of the columns of the model matrix.
X.RC residuals
the residuals from the fit.
If weights were used, then the residuals are the raw residuals - the
weights are not taken into account.
If you need residuals that all have the same variance, then use the
`residuals' function with `type="pearson"'.
X.RC fitted.values
the fitted values from the fit.
If weights were used, the fitted values are not adjusted for the weights.
X.RC family
the family of which the fitted regression model belongs, eg., 
binomial(link=probit)
X.RC bound
the (absolute) L1 constraint imposed on the parameters.
X.RC Lagrangian
the value of the Lagrangian that enforces the constraint at the solution.
X.RC xtx
the moment matrix of the variables that are under the constraint.
(After taking weights, sweep-out variables and standardization into
account).
X.RC xtr
the product of the design matrix of the variables that are under the
constraint (after taking weights, sweep-out variables and
standardization into account) with the residual vector.
X.RC constrained.coefficients
the coefficients on the scale on which they are constrained.  Useful
as initial value for further fits.
X.RC sweep.out
information on the variables that are not under the constraint and on
which the other variables and the response is projected first.
Optional, not present if `sweep.out = NULL'.
X.RC assign
the list of assignments of coefficients (and effects) to the terms in
the model.
The names of this list are the names of the terms.
The `i'th element of the list is the vector saying which coefficients
correspond to the `i'th term.
It may be of length 0 if there were no estimable effects for the term.
See also `R.assign' below.
X.RC terms
an object of mode `expression' and class `term' summarizing the formula.
Used by various methods, but typically not of direct relevance to users.
X.RC call
an image of the call that produced the object, but with the arguments
all named and with the actual formula included as the formula argument.
X.RC contrasts
a list containing sufficient information to construct the contrasts
used to fit any factors occurring in the model.
The list contains entries that are either matrices or character vectors.
When a factor is coded by contrasts, the corresponding contrast matrix
is stored in this list.
Factors that appear only as dummy variables and variables in the model
that are matrices correspond to character vectors in the list.
The character vector has the level names for a factor or the column
labels for a matrix.
X.RC x
optionally the model matrix, if `x=T'.
X.RC y
optionally the response, if `y=T'.
X.DT
The residuals, fitted values, coefficients, and effects should be extracted
by the generic functions of the same name, rather than
by the `$' operator.  
X.SA
`gl1ce', `coefficients'.
X.KW classes
X.KW regression
X.KW methods
X.WR
X
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d'`"
  test 3596 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/gl1ce.object.d: original size 3596, current size $shar_count"
fi
# ============= Lasso2/is.formula.d ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/is.formula.d' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/is.formula.d (File already exists)'
else

X.\" Copyright (C) 1998

# ============= Lasso2/l1ce.d ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/l1ce.d' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/l1ce.d (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/l1ce.d (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/l1ce.d' &&
X.BG
X.FN l1ce
X.TL
Fit a regression problem while imposing an L1 constraint on the parameters
X.DN
Returns an object of class `"l1ce"' or `"licelist"' that represents 
fit(s) of linear models while imposing L1 constraint(s) on the parameters.
X.CS
l1ce(formula, data=sys.parent(), weights, subset, na.action,
X     sweep.out= ~ 1, x=F, y=F, contrasts=NULL, standardize=T,
X     trace=F, guess.constrained.coefficients=double(p),
X     bound=0.5, absolute.t=F, ...)
X.RA
X.AG formula
a formula object, with the response on the left of a `~' operator,
and the terms, separated by `+' operators, on the right.
X.OA
X.AG data
a `data.frame' in which to interpret the variables named in the
formula, the `weights', the `subset' and the `sweep.out' argument.
If this is missing, then the variables in the formula should be on the
search list.
X.AG weights
vector of observation weights.
The length of `weights' must be the same as the number of observations.
The weights must be nonnegative and it is strongly recommended that they
be strictly positive, since zero weights are ambiguous, compared to use
of the `subset' argument.
X.AG subset
expression saying which subset of the rows of the data
should be used in the fit.
This can be a logical vector (which is replicated to have length equal
to the number of observations), or a numeric vector indicating which 
observation numbers are to be included, or a character vector of the
row names to be included.
All observations are included by default.
X.AG na.action
a function to filter missing data.
This is applied to the `model.frame' after
any `subset' argument has been used.
The default (with `na.fail') is to create an error
if any missing values are found.
A possible alternative is `na.omit', which deletes observations
that contain one or more missing values.
X.AG sweep.out
a formula object, variables whose parameters are not put under the
constraint are swept out first.  The variables should appear on the
right of a `~' operator and be separated by `+' operators.  Default is
`~1', i.e. the constant term is not under the constraint.  If this
parameter is `NULL', then all parameters are put under the constraint.
X.AG x
logical flag: if `TRUE', the model matrix is returned in component `x'.
X.AG y
logical flag: if `TRUE', the response is returned in component `y'.
X.AG contrasts
a list giving contrasts for some or all of the factors
appearing in the model formula.
The elements of the list should have the same name as the variable
and should be either a contrast matrix (specifically, any full-rank
matrix with as many rows as there are levels in the factor),
or else a function to compute such a matrix given the number of levels.
X.AG standardize
logical flag: if `TRUE', then the columns of the model matrix that
correspond to parameters that are constrained are standardized to have
emprical variance one.  The standardization is done after taking
possible weights into account and after sweeping out variables whose
parameters are not constrained.
X.AG trace
logical flag: if `TRUE', then the status during each iteration of
the fitting is reported.
X.AG guess.constrained.coefficients
initial guess for the parameters that are constrained.  
X.AG bound
numeric, either a single number or a vector: the constraint(s) that
is/are put onto the L1 norm of the parameters. 
X.AG absolute.t
logical flag: if `TRUE', then `bound' is an absolute bound and
all entries in `bound' can be any positive number.  If `FALSE', then
`bound' is a relative bound and all entries must be between 0 and 1.
X.RT
an object of class `l1ce' (if `bound' was a single value) or
`l1celist' (if `bound' was a vector of values) is returned.
See `l1ce.object' and `l1celist.object' for details.
X.SE
None
X.SH REFERENCES
Osborne, M.R., Presnell, B. and Turlach, B.A. (1999).
On the {LASSO} and its dual,
X.ul
Journal of Computational and  Graphical Statistics.
To appear.
X.sp
Tibshirani, R. (1996).
Regression shrinkage and selection via the lasso,
X.ul
Journal of the Royal Statistical Society, Series B
\fB58\fR(1), 267-288.
X.EX
l1ce(Yield ~ ., Iowa, bound = 10, trace = trace, absolute.t=T)
X
l1ce(lpsa ~ ., Prostate, bound=(1:30)/30)
X.KW models
X.KW optimize
X.KW regression
X.WR
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/l1ce.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/l1ce.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/l1ce.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/l1ce.d'`"
  test 4194 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/l1ce.d: original size 4194, current size $shar_count"
fi

X.BG
X.FN tr
X.TL
Trace of a matrix
X.DN

X.CS
tr(mat)
X.RA
X.AG mat
a square matrix
X.RT
The trace of the matrix, i.e. the sum of its diagonal elements, is returned.
X.EX
# The function is currently defined as
function(mat)
{
X  dims <- dim(mat)
X  if((length(dims) != 2) || dims[1] != dims[2])
X    stop("This function is only defined for square matrices")
X  sum(diag(mat))
}

X.\" Foundation, Inc., 59 Temple Place, Suite 330, Boston, 
X.\" MA 02111-1307 USA
X.BG D
X.FN l1ce.object
X.TL
L1 Constrainted Estimation Model Object
X.DN
These are objects of class `"l1ce"'
They represent the fit of a regression model under an L1 constraint on
(some of the parameters).
X.SH GENERATION
This class of objects is returned from the `l1ce' function
to represent a fitted model.
X.SH METHODS
The `"l1ce"' class of objects has methods for the following generic
functions:
X.br
`coef', `deviance', `fitted', `formula', `gcv', `labels', `predict',
`print', `residuals', `summary', `vcov'.
X.SH STRUCTURE
The following components must be included in a legitimate `l1ce' object.
X.RC coefficients
the coefficients of the fit of the response to the
columns of the model
matrix.
The names of the coefficients are the names of the
columns of the model matrix.
X.RC residuals
the residuals from the fit.
If weights were used, then the residuals are the raw residuals - the
weights are not taken into account.
If you need residuals that all have the same variance, then use the
`residuals' function with `type="pearson"'.
X.RC fitted.values
the fitted values from the fit.
If weights were used, the fitted values are not adjusted for the weights.
X.RC bound
the (absolute) L1 constraint imposed on the parameters.
X.RC relative.bound
optional, the (relative) L1 constraint imposed on the parameters.
Present if `absolute.t=F'.
X.RC Lagrangian
the value of the Lagrangian that enforces the constraint at the
solution.
X.RC xtx
the moment matrix of the variables that are under the constraint.
(After taking weights, sweep-out variables and standardization into
account).
X.RC xtr
the product of the design matrix of the variables that are under the
constraint (after taking weights, sweep-out variables and
standardization into account) with the residual vector.
X.RC constrained.coefficients
the coefficients on the scale on which they are constrained.  Useful
as initial value for further fits.
X.RC sweep.out
information on the variables that are not under the constraint and on
which the other variables and the response is projected first.
Optional, not present if `sweep.out = NULL'.
X.RC assign
the list of assignments of coefficients (and effects) to the terms in
the model.
The names of this list are the names of the terms.
The `i'th element of the list is the vector saying which coefficients
correspond to the `i'th term.
It may be of length 0 if there were no estimable effects for the term.
See also `R.assign' below.
X.RC terms
an object of mode `expression' and class `term' summarizing the formula.
Used by various methods, but typically not of direct relevance to users.
X.RC call
an image of the call that produced the object, but with the arguments
all named and with the actual formula included as the formula argument.
X.RC contrasts
a list containing sufficient information to construct the contrasts
used to fit any factors occurring in the model.
The list contains entries that are either matrices or character vectors.
When a factor is coded by contrasts, the corresponding contrast matrix
is stored in this list.
Factors that appear only as dummy variables and variables in the model
that are matrices correspond to character vectors in the list.
The character vector has the level names for a factor or the column
labels for a matrix.
X.RC x
optionally the model matrix, if `x=T'.
X.RC y
optionally the response, if `y=T'.
X.DT
The residuals, fitted values, coefficients, and effects should be extracted
by the generic functions of the same name, rather than
by the `$' operator.  
X.SA
`l1ce', `coefficients'.
X.KW classes
X.KW regression
X.KW methods
X.WR
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/l1ce.object.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/l1ce.object.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/l1ce.object.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/l1ce.object.d'`"
  test 4528 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/l1ce.object.d: original size 4528, current size $shar_count"
fi

X.\" MA 02111-1307 USA
X.BG D
X.FN l1celist.object
X.TL
Several L1 Constrained Estimation Model Object
X.DN
These are objects of class `"l1celist"'
They represent the fits of several regression model under an L1
constraint on (some of the parameters).
X.SH GENERATION
This class of objects is returned from the `l1ce' function
to represent a fitted model.
X.SH METHODS
The `"l1celist"' class of objects has methods for the following generic
functions:
X.br
`[', `[[', `aux', `coef', `deviance', `fitted', `formula', `gcv',
`labels', `plot', `print', `residuals', `vcov'.
X.SH STRUCTURE
An object of class `l1celist' is a list of lists.  Each component of
the list is a list with the information of an object of class `l1ce'
that is unique for that information.  All shared information is stored
as attributes. 
X
Each component of the list must include the following components 
for it to be a legitimate `l1celist' object. 
X.RC coefficients
the coefficients of the fit of the response to the
columns of the model
matrix.
The names of the coefficients are the names of the
columns of the model matrix.
X.RC residuals
the residuals from the fit.
If weights were used, then the residuals are the raw residuals - the
weights are not taken into account.
If you need residuals that all have the same variance, then use the
`residuals' function with `type="pearson"'.
X.RC fitted.values
the fitted values from the fit.
If weights were used, the fitted values are not adjusted for the weights.
X.RC bound
the (absolute) L1 constraint imposed on the parameters.
X.RC relative.bound
optional, the (relative) L1 constraint imposed on the parameters.
Present if `absolute.t=F'.
X.RC Lagrangian
the value of the Lagrangian that enforces the constraint at the
solution.
X.RC xtr
the product of the design matrix of the variables that are under the
constraint (after taking weights, sweep-out variables and
standardization into account) with the residual vector.
X.RC constrained.coefficients
the coefficients on the scale on which they are constrained.  Useful
as initial value for further fits.
X.DT
The residuals, fitted values, coefficients, and effects should be extracted
by the generic functions of the same name, rather than
by using the `[[]]' and the `$' operator.  
X.SA
`l1ce', `coefficients'.
X.KW classes
X.KW regression
X.KW methods
X.WR
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/l1celist.object.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/l1celist.object.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/l1celist.object.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/l1celist.object.d'`"
  test 3251 -eq "$shar_count" ||

X.\" License along with this library; if not, write to the Free Software
X.\" Foundation, Inc., 59 Temple Place, Suite 330, Boston, 
X.\" MA 02111-1307 USA
X.BG
X.FN plot.l1celist
X.TL
Plot a `l1celist' object
X.DN
Plots a `l1celist' object on the current graphics device.
X.CS
plot.l1celist <- function(object, plot=T, all=T, constrained=F, ...){
X.RA
X.AG object
fitted model object of class `l1celist'.
X.0A
X.AG plot
if `TRUE' a `matplot()' of all the coefficients in the list against
the relative bound (absolute bound if relative is not present) is
plotted.  Otherwise no plot is done.
X.AG all
If `FALSE', then only the non-zero coefficients are returned.
X.AG constrained
if `TRUE' then only the coefficients that were constrained
are returned.
X.RT
A matrix with the bound(s) (relative [if used] and absolute),
the Lagrangian(s) and coefficints of the fitted model(s).
X.SE
none
X.KW hplot
X.WR
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/plot.l1celist.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/plot.l1celist.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/plot.l1celist.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/plot.l1celist.d'`"
  test 1688 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/plot.l1celist.d: original size 1688, current size $shar_count"
fi
# ============= Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d' &&
X.BG
X.FN predict.gl1ce
X.TL
Use `predict()' on a `gl1ce' object
X.DN
Extracts the fitted values from a `gl1ce()' object and returns a matrix of
predictions.
X.CS
predict.gl1ce(object, newdata, type=c("link", "response"), ...)
X.RA
X.AG object
a fitted `gl1ce' object.
X.OA
X.AG newdata
a data frame containing the values at which predictions are required.
This argument can be missing, in which case predictions are made at
the same values used to compute the object.  
Only those predictors referred to in the right side of the formula in
object need be present by name in `newdata'. 
X.AG type
type of predictions, with choices "link" (the default), or "response".
The default produces predictions on the scale of the additive predictors, and 
with  newdata missing,  predict()  is  simply  an extractor function for
this component of a `gl1ce' object. If "response" is selected, the  predictions
are on the scale of the response, and are monotone transformations of the 
additive predictors, using the  inverse link function.
X.RT
a vector of predictions.
X.DT
This function is a method for the generic function predict
for  class  `gl1ce'.   It can be invoked by calling predict
for an object of the appropriate  class,  or  directly  by
calling  predict.gl1ce  regardless  of the class of the object.
X.SH WARNING
`predict' can produce incorrect predictions when the `newdata' 
argument is used if the formula in `object' involves 
data-dependent transformations, such as `poly(Age, 3)' 
or `sqrt(Age - min(Age))'.
X.WR
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d'`"
  test 1512 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/predict.gl1ce.d: original size 1512, current size $shar_count"
fi

# ============= Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d' &&
X.BG
X.FN residuals.gl1ce
X.TL
Compute Residuals for `gl1ce' Objects
X.DN
Computes one of the four types of residuals available for `gl1ce' objects.
X.CS
residuals.gl1ce(object, type=c("deviance", "pearson", "working", 
X				"response") )
X.DN
This is a method for the function residuals() for  objects inheriting from 
class `gl1ce'.  However, as several types of residuals are available for 
`gl1ce' objects, there is an additional optional argument type.
X.RA
X.AG object
an object inheriting from class `gl1ce' representing a fitted model.
X.OA
X.AG type
type of residuals, with choices "deviance",  "pearson", "working" or "response"
; the first is the default.
X.RT
A numeric vector of residuals. See Statistical Models in S for detailed 
definitions of each type of residual. The sum of squared deviance residuals 
add up to the deviance.  The pearson residuals are standardized residuals on 
the scale of the response.  The  working residuals reside on the
object, and are the residuals from the final fit. The response residuals are 
simply  y-fitted(object).  The summary() method for `gl1ce' objects produces
deviance residuals.  The residuals component of a `gl1ce' object contains the 
working residuals.
X.SH REFERENCES
Chambers,  J.M.,  and  Hastie,  T.J.  (1991).  Statistical Models in S, 
pp. 204--206.
X.WR
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d'`"
  test 1312 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/residuals.gl1ce.d: original size 1312, current size $shar_count"
fi

# ============= Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d' &&
X.BG
X.FN summary.gl1ce
X.TL
Summary Method for Generalized L1 Constrained Regression Models
X.DN
Returns a summary list for fitted generalized L1 constrained regression 
models. 
X.CS
summary.gl1ce(object)
X.RA
X.AG object
fitted `gl1ce' model object.  This is assumed to be the
result of some fit that produces an object inheriting from
the class `gl1ce', in the sense that the components returned
by the gl1ce() function will be available.
X.RT
a list is returned with the following components.
X.RC call
as contained on object
X.RC residuals
the deviance residuals, as produced by residuals(object, type = "deviance")
X.RC coefficients
the coefficients of the model.
X.RC family
the family of models to which object belongs, along with the variance and link 
functions for that model.
X.RC bound
the bound used in fitting this model
X.RC Lagrangian
the Lagrangian of the model
X.DT
This function is a method for the generic function summary for  class  `gl1ce'.
It can be invoked by calling summary for an object of the appropriate class,
or directly by calling  summary.gl1ce  regardless of the class of the object.
X.WR
X
X
X
X
X
X
X
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d'`"
  test 1117 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/summary.gl1ce.d: original size 1117, current size $shar_count"
fi

X.BG
X.FN summary.l1ce
X.TL
Summary Method for Regression Models with an L1 constraint on the
parameters. 
X.DN
Returns a summary list for a regression model with an L1 constraint on
the parameters.  A null value will be returned if printing is invoked.
X.CS
summary.lm(object,
X           correlation=T,
X           type = c("OPT", "Tibshirani"),
X           gen.inverse.diag = 0,
X           sigma = NULL)
X.RA
X.AG object
the fitted model of class `"l1ce"'.
X.OA
X.AG correlation
logical flag: if `TRUE', then the correlation matrix for the coefficients
is included in the summary.
X.AG type
whether to use the covariance formula of Osborne, Presnell and Turlach
or the formula of Tibshirani
X.AG gen.inverse.diag
if Tibshirani's formula for the covariance matrix is used, this value
is used for the diagonal elements of the generalised inverse that
appears in the formula that corresponds to parameters estimated to be
zero.  The default is 0, i.e. use the Moore-Penrose inverse.
Tibshirani's code uses gen.inverse.diag=1e11.
X.AG sigma
the residual standard error estimate.  If not provided, then it is
estimated by the deviance of the model divided by the error degrees of
freedom.
X.RT
a list is returned with the following components:
X.RC correlation
the computed correlation coefficient matrix for the coefficients in
the model. 
X.RC cov.unscaled
the unscaled covariance matrix; i.e, a matrix such that multiplying it by
an estimate of the error variance produces an estimated covariance matrix
for the coefficients.
X.RC df
the number of degrees of freedom for the model and for residuals.
X.RC coefficients
a matrix with three columns, containing the coefficients, their standard errors
and the corresponding t statistic.
X.RC residuals
the model residuals.  These are the weighted residuals if weights were given 
in the model. 
X.RC sigma
the residual standard error estimate.
X.RC terms
the terms object used in fitting this model.
X.RC call
the call object used in fitting this model.
X.RC bound
the bound used in fitting this model.
X.RC relative.bound
the relative bound used in fitting this model (may not be present)
X.RC Lagrangian
the Lagrangian of the model
X.DT
X.ME summary l1ce
X.SA
`l1ce', `l1ce.object', `summary'.
X.EX
summary(l1ce(lpsa ~ .,Prostate))
X
# Produces the following output:
Call:
X l1ce(formula = lpsa ~ ., data = Prostate)
Residuals:
X    Min      1Q Median    3Q  Max 
X -1.636 -0.4119  0.076 0.452 1.83
X
Coefficients:
X             Value Std. Error Z score Pr(>|Z|) 
(Intercept) 0.7285 1.3898     0.5242  0.6002  
X     lcavol 0.4937 0.0919     5.3711  0.0000  
X    lweight 0.2682 0.1774     1.5115  0.1307  
X        age 0.0000 0.0111     0.0000  1.0000  
X       lbph 0.0093 0.0587     0.1581  0.8744  
X        svi 0.4551 0.2525     1.8023  0.0715  
X        lcp 0.0000 0.0947     0.0000  1.0000  
X    gleason 0.0000 0.1685     0.0000  1.0000  
X      pgg45 0.0002 0.0046     0.0391  0.9688  
X
Residual standard error: 0.7595 on 88.36 degrees of freedom
The relative L1 bound was      : 0.5 
The absolute L1 bound was      : 0.9219925 
The Lagrangian for the bound is:  13.05806 
X
Correlation of Coefficients:
X        (Intercept)  lcavol lweight     age    lbph     svi     lcp gleason 
X lcavol  0.1988                                                            
lweight -0.4815     -0.2071                                                
X    age -0.3938     -0.0603 -0.0974                                        
X   lbph  0.3629     -0.0201 -0.5165 -0.1303                                
X    svi -0.0624     -0.2273 -0.1442  0.0635  0.0648                        
X    lcp  0.0457     -0.4153  0.0598  0.0665  0.0632 -0.3779                
gleason -0.7666     -0.2009  0.1163 -0.0774 -0.0617  0.1084 -0.0243        
X  pgg45  0.4988      0.0956 -0.0380 -0.0630 -0.1111 -0.1921 -0.2935 -0.6526
X.KW regression
X.WR
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/summary.l1ce.d' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/summary.l1ce.d' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/summary.l1ce.d failed'

X.TL
Variance-covariance matrix
X.DN

model objects.
X.CS
vcov(...)
X.RA
X.AG ...
Fitted model object of class `lm', `mlm', `aov', `aovlist', `glm',
`nls', `l1ce' or `l1celist'.
X.RT
Estimated variance-covariance matrix of the regression coefficients.
X.SE
None
X.DT
Simple extraction method function.

X.BG
X.FN vcov.l1ce
X.TL
Use `vcov()' on a `l1ce' object.
X.CS
vcov(object, type = c("OPT", "Tibshirani"), gen.inverse.diag = 0)
X.RA
X.AG object
a `l1ce' object
X.OA
X.AG type
whether to use the covariance formula of Osborne, Presnell and Turlach
or the formula of Tibshirani
X.AG gen.inverse.diag
if Tibshirani's formula for the covariance matrix is used, this value
is used for the diagonal elements of the generalised inverse that
appears in the formula that corresponds to parameters estimated to be
zero.  The default is 0, i.e. use the Moore-Penrose inverse.
Tibshirani's code uses gen.inverse.diag=1e11.
X.DN
This is a method for the function `vcov()' for objects inheriting
from class `l1ce'.
See `vcov' for the general behavior of this function.
X.DT
See documentation.
X.WR
SHAR_EOF

".First.lib"<-
X  function(...)
{
X  dyn.load.lib(...,basename="Lasso2")
X  cat("Library to solve regression problems while imposing\n")
X  cat("an L1 constraint on the parameters. Release 2.1\n")
X  cat("Copyright (C) 1998, 1999\n")
X  cat("Justin Lokhorst <jlokhors@stats.adelaide.edu.au>\n")
X  cat("Berwin A. Turlach <bturlach@stats.adelaide.edu.au>\n")
X  cat("Bill Venables <wvenable@stats.adelaide.edu.au>\n\n")
}
X
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/First.lib.q' &&
  chmod 0644 'Lasso2/First.lib.q' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/First.lib.q failed'

  test 1435 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/First.lib.q: original size 1435, current size $shar_count"
fi

# ============= Lasso2/coef.q ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/coef.q' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/coef.q (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/coef.q (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/coef.q' &&
###  Copyright (C) 1998
###  Berwin A. Turlach <bturlach@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###  Bill Venables <wvenable@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###
###  This library is free software; you can redistribute it and/or
###  modify it under the terms of the GNU Library General Public
###  License as published by the Free Software Foundation; either
###  version 2 of the License, or (at your option) any later version.
###
###  This library is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
###  but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
###  MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the GNU
###  Library General Public License for more details.
###
###  You should have received a copy of the GNU Library General Public
###  License along with this library; if not, write to the Free Software
###  Foundation, Inc., 59 Temple Place, Suite 330, Boston, 
###  MA 02111-1307 USA
coef.l1ce <- function(object, all=T, constrained=F, ...){
X  label <- if(constrained) "constrained.coefficients" else 
X      "coefficients"
X  if(all) {
X    object[[label]]
X  }
X  else {
X    object[[label]][abs(object[[label]]) > sqrt(.Machine$double.eps)]
X  }
}
X
coef.l1celist <- function(object, all=T, constrained=F, ...){
X  label <- if(constrained) "constrained.coefficients" else 
X      "coefficients"
X  if(all) {
X    do.call("rbind", lapply(object, "[[", label))
X  }
X  else {
X    junk <- do.call("rbind", lapply(object, "[[", label))
X    ind <- apply(abs(junk), 2, sum)
X    junk[, ind != 0]
X  }
}
X
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/coef.q' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/coef.q' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/coef.q failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/coef.q'`"
  test 1502 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/coef.q: original size 1502, current size $shar_count"
fi
# ============= Lasso2/deviance.q ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/deviance.q' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/deviance.q (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/deviance.q (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/deviance.q' &&
###  Copyright (C) 1998, 1999
###  Justin Lokhorst <jlokhors@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###  Berwin A. Turlach <bturlach@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###  Bill Venables <wvenable@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###
###  This library is free software; you can redistribute it and/or
###  modify it under the terms of the GNU Library General Public
###  License as published by the Free Software Foundation; either
###  version 2 of the License, or (at your option) any later version.
###
###  This library is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
###  but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
###  MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the GNU
###  Library General Public License for more details.
###
###  You should have received a copy of the GNU Library General Public
###  License along with this library; if not, write to the Free Software
###  Foundation, Inc., 59 Temple Place, Suite 330, Boston, 
###  MA 02111-1307 USA
deviance.l1ce <- function(object, ...){
X  if(is.null(w <- object$weights)){
X    sum(object$residuals^2)
X  }else{
X    sum(w * object$residuals^2)
X  }
}
X
deviance.l1celist <- function(object, ...){
X  
X  resid <- do.call("cbind", lapply(object, "[[", "residuals"))
X  weights <- attr(object, "weights")
X  if(is.null(weights)){
X    apply(resid^2,2,sum)
X  }else{
X    apply(weights*resid^2,2,sum)
X  }
}
X
deviance.gl1ce <- function(object, ...) {
X  object$deviance
}
X
X
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/deviance.q' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/deviance.q' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/deviance.q failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/deviance.q'`"
  test 1422 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/deviance.q: original size 1422, current size $shar_count"
fi

  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/fitted.q' &&

fitted.l1ce <- function(object, ...){
X  object$fitted
}
X
fitted.l1celist <- function(object, ...){
X  do.call("cbind", lapply(object, "[[", "fitted"))
}
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/fitted.q' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/fitted.q' ||

###  Copyright (C) 1998

is.formula <- function(f){
X  inherits(f, "formula")
}
X
merge.formula <- function(f1,f2){
X
X  if(!(is.formula(f1) && length(f1) == 3))
X    stop("First argument is invalid")
X
X  if(!is.formula(f2))
X    stop("Second argument is invalid")
X
X  str <- paste(c(deparse(f1[[2]]), "~",
X                 deparse(f1[[3]]), "+", 
X                 deparse(f2[[length(f2)]])), collapse = "")
X  as.formula(str)
X
}
X
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/formula.util.q' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/formula.util.q' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/formula.util.q failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/formula.util.q'`"
  test 1298 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/formula.util.q: original size 1298, current size $shar_count"
fi

  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/gcv.q' &&
###  Copyright (C) 1998
###  Berwin A. Turlach <bturlach@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###  Bill Venables <wvenable@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###
###  This library is free software; you can redistribute it and/or
###  modify it under the terms of the GNU Library General Public
###  License as published by the Free Software Foundation; either
###  version 2 of the License, or (at your option) any later version.
###
###  This library is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
###  but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
###  MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the GNU
###  Library General Public License for more details.
###
###  You should have received a copy of the GNU Library General Public
###  License along with this library; if not, write to the Free Software
###  Foundation, Inc., 59 Temple Place, Suite 330, Boston, 
###  MA 02111-1307 USA
gcv <- function(object, ...)
X  UseMethod("gcv")
X
gcv.l1ce <- function(object,
X                     type = c("OPT", "Tibshirani"),
X                     gen.inverse.diag = 0)
{
X  type <- match.arg(type)
X
X  covdf <- vcov(object,type,gen.inverse.diag)
X  rss  <- deviance(object)
X
X  n <- length(object$fitted)
X  res <- rss/((1-covdf$df[1]/n)^2*n)
X  
X  cbind(bound=object$bound, gcv=res)
}
X
gcv.l1celist <- function(object,
X                         type = c("OPT", "Tibshirani"),
X                         gen.inverse.diag = 0)
{
X  type <- match.arg(type)
X  
X  covdf <- vcov(object,type,gen.inverse.diag)
X  rss  <- deviance(object)
X  
X  rssdf <- do.call("rbind",lapply(covdf, "[[", "df"))[,1]
X  n <- length(object[[1]]$fitted)
X  res <- rss/((1-rssdf/n)^2*n)
X
X  cbind(bound=aux(object), gcv = res)
}
X
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/gcv.q' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/gcv.q' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/gcv.q failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/gcv.q'`"
  test 1694 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/gcv.q: original size 1694, current size $shar_count"
fi
# ============= Lasso2/gl1ce.q ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/gl1ce.q' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/gl1ce.q (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/gl1ce.q (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/gl1ce.q' &&
###  Copyright (C) 1999
###  Justin Lokhorst <jlokhors@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###  Berwin A. Turlach <bturlach@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###  Bill Venables <wvenable@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###
###  This library is free software; you can redistribute it and/or
###  modify it under the terms of the GNU Library General Public
###  License as published by the Free Software Foundation; either
###  version 2 of the License, or (at your option) any later version.
###
###  This library is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
###  but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
###  MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the GNU
###  Library General Public License for more details.
###
###  You should have received a copy of the GNU Library General Public
###  License along with this library; if not, write to the Free Software
###  Foundation, Inc., 59 Temple Place, Suite 330, Boston, 
###  MA 02111-1307 USA
gl1ce <- function(formula, data = sys.parent(), weights, subset, na.action,
X                  family = gaussian, control = glm.control(...),
X                  sweep.out = ~ 1,
X                  x = F, y = T,
X                  contrasts = NULL,
X                  standardize = T, 
X                  guess.constrained.coefficients = double(p),
X                  bound = 0.5,...)
{
X  call <- match.call()
X  m <- match.call(expand = F)
X
X  m$sweep.out <- m$x <- m$y <- m$contrasts <- m$standardize <-
X    m$guess.constrained.coefficients <- m$trace <- m$bound <-
X      m$family <- m$control <- m$... <- NULL
X  
X  something.to.sweep.out <- !is.null(sweep.out)
X
X  if(something.to.sweep.out) {
X    m$formula <- merge.formula(formula, sweep.out)
X  }
X
X  m[[1]] <- as.name("model.frame")
X  if(!missing(data) && !is.data.frame(data)) {
X    m$data <- data <- as.data.frame(data)
X    warning(paste(deparse(substitute(data)), "is not a dataframe"))
X  }
X
X  m <- eval(m, data)
X  weights <- model.extract(m, weights)
X  Y <- model.extract(m, response)
X  Terms <- terms(formula, data = data)
X  X <- model.matrix(Terms, m, contrasts)
X  X.names <- dimnames(X)[[2]]
X  maxit <- control$maxit
X  epsilon <- control$epsilon
X  trace <- control$trace
X  offset <- model.extract(m,offset)
X  Y.to.C <- Y
X
X  family <- as.family(family)
X  link <- family$link
X  inv.link <- family$inverse
X  deriv.link <- family$deriv
X  variance.function <- family$variance    
X  
X  if(!length(weights))
X    weights <- rep(1, length(Y.to.C))
X  else if(any(weights < 0))
X    stop("Negative weights not allowed")
X
X  if(any(weights == 0)) {
X    stop("The subset argument should be used for observations that
X             need to be excluded")
X  }
X    
X  if(family$family[[1]] == "Binomial") {
X    mu <- (Y.to.C + (1/2))/(weights + 1)
X  }
X  else {
X    mu <- (Y.to.C + mean(Y))/2
X  }
X  
X
X  eta <- link(mu) - offset
X
X  j <- 0 
X  
X  if(something.to.sweep.out) {
X    X.sweep.out <- model.matrix(terms(sweep.out, data = data), m, 
X                                contrasts)
X    X.sweep.out.names <- dimnames(X.sweep.out)[[2]]
X    name.matches <- match(X.sweep.out.names, X.names)
X    all.matched <- !any(is.na(name.matches))
X
X    if(!all.matched)
X      warning("Variables in \"sweep.out\" are not a subset of
X                   variables in \"formula\"")
X    
X    name.matches <- name.matches[!is.na(name.matches)]
X    if(some.matched <- length(name.matches)) {
X      X.to.C <- X[,  - name.matches, drop = F]        
X      X.names <- X.names[ - name.matches]
X      if(length(X.to.C) == 0)
X        stop("Do you really want to sweep out all the variables?")
X    }else{
X      X.to.C <- X
X    }
X  }else {
X    X.to.C <- X     
X  }
X  
X  n <- nrow(X.to.C)
X  p <- ncol(X.to.C)
X
X  if(length(guess.constrained.coefficients) != p)
X    stop("invalid argument for \"guess.constrained.coefficients\"")
X
X  keep <- c("coefficients", "fitted.values", "residuals", "success", 
X            "Lagrangian", "bound")
X  check <- 1
X
X  if(something.to.sweep.out) {
X    check.vector <- rep(0, ncol(X))
X  }
X  else {
X    check.vector <- rep(0, ncol(X.to.C))
X  }
X
X  continue <- T
X
X  while(continue) {
X
X    M <- deriv.link(mu)
X    Y.to.C <- eta + (Y - mu) * M
X    W <- sqrt(weights/(variance.function(mu) * (M^2)))
X
X    X.to.C.w <- X.to.C * W
X    
X
X    Y.to.C <- Y.to.C * W    
X
X    if(something.to.sweep.out) {
X      X.sweep.out.w <- X.sweep.out * W
X
X      X.so.qr <- qr(X.sweep.out.w)
X      X.so.coefficients <- qr.coef(X.so.qr, Y.to.C)   #beta
X      X.to.C.w <- qr.resid(X.so.qr, X.to.C.w) #Z*
X      Y.to.C <- qr.resid(X.so.qr, Y.to.C)     #Y*
X    }
X
X    if(standardize) {
X      X.to.C.stds <- sqrt(apply(X.to.C.w, 2, var))
X      if(any(X.to.C.stds < sqrt(.Machine$double.eps)))
X        stop("Matrix build from transformed variables has
X               a constant column")
X      X.to.C.w <- sweep(X.to.C.w, 2, X.to.C.stds, "/")
X    }
X    
X    check.vector.old <- check.vector        
X
X    fit <- .C("lasso",
X              X = as.double(X.to.C.w),
X              n = as.integer(n),
X              p = as.integer(p),
X              bound = as.double(bound),
X              coefficients = as.double(guess.constrained.coefficients),
X              Y = as.double(Y.to.C),
X              fitted.values = double(n),
X              residuals = double(n),
X              Lagrangian = double(1),
X              success = integer(1),
X              trace = as.logical(trace),
X              assub = as.logical(F))[keep]
X
X    if(fit$success < 0) {
X      stop("Uups, something went wrong in the C-routine")
X    }
X    else {
X      fit$success <- NULL
X    }
X
X    guess.constrained.coefficients <- gamma <- fit$coefficients     
X    
X    if(something.to.sweep.out) {
X      check.vector <- c(X.so.coefficients, gamma)
X    }
X    else {
X      check.vector <- gamma
X    }
X
X    eta <- as.vector((X.to.C.w %*% gamma + X.sweep.out.w %*% 
X             X.so.coefficients)/W)
X    mu <- inv.link(eta + offset)    ###Our new values of mu and eta
X
X    check <- (sum((check.vector - check.vector.old)^2))/(sum(check.vector^2))
X    j <- j + 1
X
X    continue <- (j < maxit) && (check > epsilon)
X
X  }
X
X  if(j == maxit) {
X    warning("Maximal number of iterations reached.")
X  }
X
X  fit$iter <- j
X  deviance <- family$deviance(mu, Y, weights)
X  fit$linear.predictors <- eta
X  
X  fit$xtx <- crossprod(X.to.C)
X  fit$xtr <- crossprod(X.to.C,fit$residuals)
X  fit$constrained.coefficients <- fit$coefficients
X  names(fit$coefficients) <- names(fit$constrained.coefficients) <- 
X    dimnames(X.to.C)[[2]]
X  if(standardize) {
X    fit$X.stds <- X.to.C.stds
X    fit$coefficients <- fit$coefficients/X.to.C.stds
X  }
X  if(something.to.sweep.out) {
X    X.so.X <- qr.coef(X.so.qr, X.to.C)
X    X.so.Y.fit <- qr.fitted(X.so.qr, Y.to.C)
X    fit$fitted.values <- fit$fitted.values + X.so.Y.fit
X    X.so.coefficients <- X.so.coefficients - X.so.X %*% fit$coefficients
X    tmp <- fit$coefficients
X    fit$coefficients <- rep(0, ncol(X))
X    names(fit$coefficients) <- dimnames(X)[[2]]
X    fit$coefficients[X.names] <- tmp
X    names(X.so.coefficients) <- X.sweep.out.names
X    ind <- names(fit$coefficients[name.matches])
X    fit$coefficients[name.matches] <- X.so.coeff[ind]
X    fit$sweep.out <- list(sweep.out = sweep.out, X.sweep.out.names
X                          = X.sweep.out.names, name.matches = name.matches, 
X                          all.matched = all.matched, some.matched = some.matched, 
X                          X.so.rtr.inv = qr.rtr.inv(X.so.qr), X.so.X = X.so.X)
X  }
X  fit$weights <- W
X  fit$prior.weights <- weights
X  fit$terms <- Terms
X  fit$call <- call
X  fit$contrasts <- attr(X, "contrasts")
X  fit$assign <- attr(X, "assign")
X  fit$family <- family
X  fit$deviance <- deviance
X  if(x)
X    fit$x <- X
X  if(y) fit$y <- Y
X  ##    if(!absolute.t)
X  ##      fit$relative.bound <- relative.bound
X  structure(fit, class = c("gl1ce", "l1ce"), na.message = attr(m, "na.message"))
}
X
X
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/gl1ce.q' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/gl1ce.q' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/gl1ce.q failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/gl1ce.q'`"
  test 7796 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/gl1ce.q: original size 7796, current size $shar_count"
fi
# ============= Lasso2/l1ce.q ==============
if test -f 'Lasso2/l1ce.q' && test X"$1" != X"-c"; then
  echo 'x - skipping Lasso2/l1ce.q (File already exists)'
else
  echo 'x - extracting Lasso2/l1ce.q (text)'
  sed 's/^X//' << 'SHAR_EOF' > 'Lasso2/l1ce.q' &&
###  Copyright (C) 1998
###  Berwin A. Turlach <bturlach@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###  Bill Venables <wvenable@stats.adelaide.edu.au>
###
###  This library is free software; you can redistribute it and/or
###  modify it under the terms of the GNU Library General Public
###  License as published by the Free Software Foundation; either
###  version 2 of the License, or (at your option) any later version.
###
###  This library is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
###  but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
###  MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the GNU
###  Library General Public License for more details.
###
###  You should have received a copy of the GNU Library General Public
###  License along with this library; if not, write to the Free Software
###  Foundation, Inc., 59 Temple Place, Suite 330, Boston, 
###  MA 02111-1307 USA
l1ce <- function(formula, data = sys.parent(), weights, subset, na.action,
X                 sweep.out = ~ 1,
X		 x = F, y = F, contrasts = NULL,
X                 standardize = T,
X		 trace = F,
X                 guess.constrained.coefficients = double(p),
X		 bound = 0.5,
X                 absolute.t = F) {
X
X  call <- match.call()
X  m <- match.call(expand = F)
X  m$sweep.out <- m$x <- m$y <- m$contrasts <-
X    m$standardize <- m$guess.constrained.coefficients <- m$trace <- 
X      m$bound <- m$absolute.t <- NULL  
X  
X  something.to.sweep.out <- !is.null(sweep.out)
X  if(something.to.sweep.out){
X    m$formula <- merge.formula(formula,sweep.out)
X  }
X  m[[1]] <- as.name("model.frame")
X
X  if(!missing(data) && !is.data.frame(data)){
X    m$data <- data <- as.data.frame(data)
X    warning(paste(deparse(substitute(data)),
X                  "is not a dataframe"))
X  }
X
X  m <- eval(m, data)
X  weights <- model.extract(m, weights)
X  Y <- model.extract(m, response)
X  Terms <- terms(formula, data=data)
X  X <- model.matrix(Terms, m, contrasts)
X  X.names <- dimnames(X)[[2]]
X
X  X.to.C <- X
X  Y.to.C <- Y
X
X  if(weighted <- length(weights)) { 
X    Y.to.C <- Y.to.C * (w <- sqrt(weights))
X    X.to.C <- X.to.C * w
X  }
X
X  if(something.to.sweep.out){
X    sweep.out[[3]] <- sweep.out[[2]]
X    sweep.out[[2]] <- formula[[2]]
X    X.sweep.out <- model.matrix(terms(sweep.out, data=data),
X                                m, contrasts)
X    X.sweep.out.names <- dimnames(X.sweep.out)[[2]]
X    if(weighted){
X      X.sweep.out <- X.sweep.out * w
X    }
X
X    name.matches<- match(X.sweep.out.names,X.names)
X    all.matched <- !any(is.na(name.matches))
X    if(!all.matched)
X      warning("Variables in \"sweep.out\" are not a subset of variables in \"formula\"")
X
X    name.matches <- name.matches[!is.na(name.matches)]
X    if(some.matched <- length(name.matches)){
X      X.to.C <- X.to.C[,-name.matches,drop=F]
X      X.names <- X.names[-name.matches]
X      if( length(X.to.C) == 0 )
X        stop("Do you really want to sweep out all the variables?")
X    }
X
X    X.so.qr <- qr(X.sweep.out)
X    if( X.so.qr$rank != ncol(X.sweep.out) )
X      warning("Matrix build from variables in \"sweep.out\" is rank deficient")
X    
X    X.so.coefficients <- qr.coef(X.so.qr,Y.to.C)
X    X.so.X  <- qr.coef(X.so.qr,X.to.C)
X    X.so.Y.fit <- qr.fitted(X.so.qr,Y.to.C)
X    X.to.C  <- qr.resid(X.so.qr,X.to.C)
X    Y.to.C  <- qr.resid(X.so.qr,Y.to.C)
X  }
X  
X  if(standardize){
X    X.to.C.stds<-sqrt(apply(X.to.C,2,var))
X    if( any(X.to.C.stds < sqrt(.Machine$double.eps)) )
X      stop("Matrix build from transformed variables has a constant column") 
X
X    X.to.C <- sweep(X.to.C,2,X.to.C.stds,"/")
X  }
X   
X  if(!absolute.t){
X    X.to.C.qr <- qr(X.to.C)
X    if( X.to.C.qr$rank != ncol(X.to.C) ){
X      warning("Matrix build from transformed variables rank deficient")
X    }else if( X.to.C.qr$rank == 0 ){
X      stop("Matrix build from transformed variables is null matrix")
X    }
X    t0 <- sum(abs(qr.coef(X.to.C.qr,Y.to.C)))
X    if( any(bound > 1) ){
X      stop("\"bound\"(s) must be between 0 and 1 if absolute.t=F")
X    }
X    bound <- (relative.bound <- bound)*t0
X  }
X  if( any(bound < 0) )
X    stop("\"bound\"(s) must be non negative")
X
X  n <- nrow(X.to.C)
X  p <- ncol(X.to.C)
X  if( length(guess.constrained.coefficients) != p )
X    stop("invalid argument for \"guess.constrained.coefficients\"")
X
X  keep <- c("coefficients", "fitted.values", "residuals", "success",
X            "Lagrangian", "bound")
X
X  if( 1 == (num.bound <- length(bound)) ){
X
X    fit <- .C("lasso",
X              X=as.double(X.to.C), n=as.integer(n), p=as.integer(p),
X              bound=as.double(bound),
X              coefficients=as.double(guess.constrained.coefficients),
X              Y=as.double(Y.to.C),
X              fitted.values=double(n), residuals=double(n),
X              Lagrangian=double(1),
X              success=integer(1), 
X              trace=as.logical(trace), 
X              assub=as.logical(F))[keep]
X    if( fit$success < 0 ){
X      stop("Uups, something went wrong in the C-routine")
X    }else{
X      fit$success <- NULL
X    }
X
X    fit$xtx <- crossprod(X.to.C)
X    fit$xtr <- crossprod(X.to.C,fit$residuals)
X    fit$constrained.coefficients <- fit$coefficients
X    names(fit$coefficients) <- names(fit$constrained.coefficients) <-
X      dimnames(X.to.C)[[2]] 
X
X    if(standardize){
X      fit$X.stds <- X.to.C.stds
X      fit$coefficients   <- fit$coefficients / X.to.C.stds
X    }
X
X    if(something.to.sweep.out){
X      fit$fitted.values <- fit$fitted.values + X.so.Y.fit
X      X.so.coefficients <- X.so.coefficients - X.so.X %*% fit$coefficients
X    
X      tmp <- fit$coefficients
X      fit$coefficients <- rep(0,ncol(X))
X      names(fit$coefficients) <- dimnames(X)[[2]]
X      fit$coefficients[X.names] <- tmp
X      names(X.so.coefficients) <- X.sweep.out.names
X      ind <- names(fit$coefficients[name.matches])
X      fit$coefficients[name.matches] <- X.so.coeff[ind]
X
X      fit$sweep.out <- list(sweep.out = sweep.out,
X                            X.sweep.out.names = X.sweep.out.names,
X                            name.matches = name.matches,
X                            all.matched = all.matched,
X                            some.matched = some.matched,
X                            X.so.rtr.inv = qr.rtr.inv(X.so.qr),
X                            X.so.X = X.so.X)
X    }
X
X    if(weighted){
X      fit$weights <- weights
X      if( any(weights==0) ){
X        fit$fitted.values <- X %*% fit$coefficients
X        fit$residuals <- Y - fit$fitted.values
X      }else{
X        fit$fitted.values <- fit$fitted.values / w
X        fit$residuals <- fit$residuals / w
X      }
X    }
X
X    fit$terms <- Terms
X    fit$call <- call
X    fit$contrasts <- attr(X, "contrasts")
X    fit$assign <- attr(X, "assign")
X    if(x)
X      fit$x <- X
X    if(y)
X      fit$y <- Y
X    if(!absolute.t)
X      fit$relative.bound <- relative.bound
X    structure(fit, class = "l1ce", 
X              na.message = attr(m, "na.message"))
X  }else{
X
X    ordered.bound <- order(bound)
X    guess.constraint.coefficients <-
X      rep(guess.constrained.coefficients,num.bound)
X    
X    res <- .C("mult_lasso",
X              X=as.double(X.to.C), n=as.integer(n), p=as.integer(p),
X              bound=as.double(bound[ordered.bound]),
X              l=as.integer(num.bound),
X              coefficients=as.double(guess.constraint.coefficients),
X              Y=as.double(Y.to.C),
X              fitted.values=double(n*num.bound),
X              residuals=double(n*num.bound),
X              Lagrangian=double(num.bound),
X              success=integer(1), 
X              trace=as.logical(trace))[keep]
X    if( res$success < 0 ){
X      stop("Uups, something went wrong in the C-routine")
X    }else{
X      res$success <- NULL
X    }
X
X    total.fit <- list()
X    ind1 <- 1:n 
X    ind2 <- 1:p 
X    for(i in 1:num.bound){
X
X      fit <- list()
X      fit$constrained.coefficients <- fit$coefficients <-
X        res$coefficients[ind2]
X      names(fit$coefficients) <- names(fit$constrained.coefficients) <-
X        dimnames(X.to.C)[[2]]
X      fit$fitted.values <- res$fitted.values[ind1]
X      fit$residuals <- res$residuals[ind1]
X      fit$bound <- res$bound[i]
X      fit$Lagrangian <- res$Lagrangian[i]
X      fit$xtr <- crossprod(X.to.C,fit$residuals)
X
X      if(standardize){
X        fit$coefficients   <- fit$coefficients / X.to.C.stds
X      }
X
X      if(something.to.sweep.out){
X        fit$fitted.values <- fit$fitted.values + X.so.Y.fit
X        X.so.coeff <- X.so.coefficients - X.so.X %*% fit$coefficients
X    
X        tmp <- fit$coefficients
X        fit$coefficients <- rep(0,ncol(X))
X        names(fit$coefficients) <- dimnames(X)[[2]]
X        fit$coefficients[X.names] <- tmp
X        names(X.so.coeff) <- X.sweep.out.names
X        ind <- names(fit$coefficients[name.matches])
X        fit$coefficients[name.matches] <- X.so.coeff[ind]
X      }
X
X      if(weighted){
X        if( any(weights==0) ){
X          fit$fitted.values <- X %*% fit$coefficients
X          fit$residuals <- Y - fit$fitted.values
X        }else{
X          fit$fitted.values <- fit$fitted.values / w
X          fit$residuals <- fit$residuals / w
X        }
X      }
X
X      if(!absolute.t)
X        fit$relative.bound <- relative.bound[ordered.bound[i]]
X                                                       
X      total.fit[[ordered.bound[i]]] <- fit
X      ind1 <- ind1 + n
X      ind2 <- ind2 + p
X    }
X
X    if(standardize){
X      attr(total.fit, "X.stds")
X    }
X    if(something.to.sweep.out){
X      attr(total.fit, "sweep.out") <-
X        list(sweep.out = sweep.out,
X             X.sweep.out.names = X.sweep.out.names,
X             name.matches = name.matches,
X             all.matched = all.matched,
X             some.matched = some.matched,
X             X.so.rtr.inv = qr.rtr.inv(X.so.qr),
X             X.so.X = X.so.X)
X    }
X    attr(total.fit, "xtx") <- crossprod(X.to.C)
X    if(weighted){
X      attr(total.fit, "weights") <- weights
X    }
X    attr(total.fit, "terms") <- Terms
X    attr(total.fit, "call") <- call
X    attr(total.fit, "contrasts") <- attr(X, "contrasts")
X    attr(total.fit, "assign") <- attr(X, "assign")
X    if(x)
X      attr(total.fit, "x") <- X
X    if(y)
X      attr(total.fit, "y") <- Y
X    structure(total.fit, class = "l1celist", 
X              na.message = attr(m, "na.message"))
X
X  }
}
SHAR_EOF
  $shar_touch -am 1209101399 'Lasso2/l1ce.q' &&
  chmod 0444 'Lasso2/l1ce.q' ||
  echo 'restore of Lasso2/l1ce.q failed'
  shar_count="`wc -c < 'Lasso2/l1ce.q'`"
  test 10170 -eq "$shar_count" ||
    echo "Lasso2/l1ce.q: original size 10170, current size $shar_count"
fi

labels.l1ce <- function(object, ...)
{
X  TL <- object$terms
X  if(!is.null(TL)) {
X    TL <- attr(TL, "term.labels")
X    TA <- object$assign
X    if(!is.null(TA)) {
X      TA <- names(TA)
X      TL <- TL[match(TA, TL, 0)]
X    }
X  }
X  TL
}
X
labels.l1celist <- function(object, ...)
{
X  TL <- attr(object, "terms")
X  if(!is.null(TL)) {
X    TL <- attr(TL, "term.labels")
X    TA <- object$assign
X    if(!is.null(TA)) {
X      TA <- names(TA)
X      TL <- TL[match(TA, TL, 0)]
X    }
X  }
X  TL
}

###  Copyright (C) 1998
